To multiply these two numbers in base 6, we can use the standard multiplication method.

\[
\begin{array}{c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c}
& & & 4 & 5 & 3 & 0 & 0 & 0_{6} \\
\times & & & 1 & 5 & 0 & 1 & 3 & 5_{6} \\
\hline
& & & & & & 3 & 2 & 5_{6} \\
& & & & 4 & 5 & 3 & 0 & 0_{6} \\
& & 2 & 2 & 6 & 3 & 3 & 2 & 0_{6} \\
\hline
& 2 & 4 & 2 & 3 & 1 & 0 & 5 & 0 & 0_{6} \\
\end{array}
\]

The result of \(453000_6 \times 150135_6\) is \(242310500_{6}\).